00:23:01.278 --> 00:23:03.780
She was there from the very beginning.

00:23:04.406 --> 00:23:06.658
From the moment I opened
my eyes to the world.

00:23:09.786 --> 00:23:12.080
The girl I first loved.

00:23:13.874 --> 00:23:15.626
The girl who made me write music,

00:23:15.876 --> 00:23:17.085
love music,

00:23:17.878 --> 00:23:19.254
and embrace my passion.

00:23:21.131 --> 00:23:25.010
The girl who listened, stayed beside me
even before the public knew me.

00:23:26.136 --> 00:23:28.180
She was there before
all of you ever met me.

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:32.142
She was there when I was a nobody.

00:23:36.897 --> 00:23:39.942
Larkin, you said,
"The only girl I've ever loved."

00:23:39.942 --> 00:23:44.196
So, does that mean
Clea Aguilar doesn't count?

00:23:45.572 --> 00:23:46.573
Yes.

00:23:47.366 --> 00:23:49.451
Clea and I were never in a relationship.

00:23:50.243 --> 00:23:52.871
We've always been just
friends and workmates.

00:23:54.164 --> 00:23:56.875
But why did you lie
to the public before?

00:23:58.251 --> 00:24:00.128
Because I didn't know any better.

00:24:01.380 --> 00:24:03.966
I wanted to succeed
so badly in the industry.

00:24:04.383 --> 00:24:08.053
I agreed to the contract where
Clea and I would be in a love team

00:24:08.474 --> 00:24:10.351
and pretend we were
together in real life.

00:24:11.932 --> 00:24:14.309
We helped each other
fulfill the agreement.

00:24:15.227 --> 00:24:17.312
All for the sake of our dreams.

00:24:19.064 --> 00:24:21.024
We pretended we were dating

00:24:21.608 --> 00:24:24.820
while being in love with different
people behind the camera.

00:24:26.530 --> 00:24:28.323
I regret all of that.

00:24:29.157 --> 00:24:31.660
I know I hurt a lot of people.

00:24:32.452 --> 00:24:33.453
And I want...

00:24:34.037 --> 00:24:35.789
I want to apologize to everyone.

00:24:47.926 --> 00:24:53.265
To my fans, Clea's fans, ArClea's fans,

00:24:55.892 --> 00:24:59.604
and especially to you,
Via, I'm very sorry.

00:25:02.816 --> 00:25:05.068
How is your relationship with Clea now?

00:25:06.319 --> 00:25:07.487
We're still friends.

00:25:07.904 --> 00:25:08.864
Just friends.

00:25:09.906 --> 00:25:11.700
I really admire Clea.

00:25:11.700 --> 00:25:14.369
She's one of the best people
I've ever worked with.

00:25:14.578 --> 00:25:18.582
She's helped me and protected
me countless times in the industry.

00:25:20.208 --> 00:25:22.836
And I feel bad that she's still
getting dragged into all of this.

00:25:24.384 --> 00:25:25.385
To Clea,

00:25:27.883 --> 00:25:30.135
I want to apologize and
also say thank you.

00:25:33.847 --> 00:25:38.393
Why did it take you so long to tell us the
truth about you and the person you love?

00:25:43.523 --> 00:25:45.275
Because I was just a kid back then.

00:25:46.735 --> 00:25:48.862
I was lost and scared.

00:25:49.988 --> 00:25:52.866
If I could do it all over again,

00:25:57.829 --> 00:26:00.916
I would shout to the whole
world how much I love Via.

00:26:12.594 --> 00:26:17.588
Hearing it from you, I just know that
she's an amazing and truly lovely girl.

00:26:24.920 --> 00:26:26.255
She is.

00:26:31.530 --> 00:26:36.034
So, do you have any message
for your fans and everyone watching?

00:26:40.997 --> 00:26:42.624
I've told you the truth now.

00:26:43.458 --> 00:26:45.585
It's up to you how you take it.

00:26:46.169 --> 00:26:47.546
I have nothing to hide.

00:26:49.548 --> 00:26:52.050
There are things I still
want to keep private, too.

00:26:52.676 --> 00:26:55.053
I know I'm in the
spotlight most of the time,

00:26:55.554 --> 00:26:58.140
but what you see in front
of the camera isn't all of me.

00:26:58.932 --> 00:27:02.310
I still value the things
I have left just for myself.

00:27:03.019 --> 00:27:04.604
I hope you all can respect that.

00:27:06.148 --> 00:27:08.817
The people you see on-screen,

00:27:09.234 --> 00:27:11.444
they're human, too, just like you.

00:27:12.821 --> 00:27:13.989
And just like you,

00:27:15.699 --> 00:27:18.118
we also want to live freely.

00:27:20.704 --> 00:27:22.455
That's all I ask from you.

00:28:04.338 --> 00:28:06.590
Finally! The truth.

00:28:06.615 --> 00:28:08.867
Darn, I feel bad for the girl.

00:28:08.892 --> 00:28:11.416
Arkin was so young back then,
that's why this happened.

00:28:11.441 --> 00:28:13.235
Let them love each other!

00:28:13.465 --> 00:28:18.136
Stop bashing, guys! She stayed quiet to
protect Arkin's career. That's true love.

00:28:18.136 --> 00:28:21.223
These online bashers really
have no life outside the Internet!

00:28:21.223 --> 00:28:23.225
Just dummy accounts everywhere!

00:28:23.266 --> 00:28:26.144
Let's learn from this, everyone.
They're human too.

00:28:26.144 --> 00:28:27.687
This is going to ruin Larkin.

00:28:27.687 --> 00:28:29.189
Larkin's got guts.

00:28:29.189 --> 00:28:30.857
Screw this industry, seriously.

00:28:30.857 --> 00:28:33.276
To everyone at Cloud Entertainment,
you're all so stupid!

00:28:56.758 --> 00:28:57.884
Hello?

00:28:59.761 --> 00:29:01.596
Is this Dr. Peja?

00:29:15.902 --> 00:29:17.570
So bright, huh?

00:29:18.738 --> 00:29:21.241
But a little sunlight
is good and healthy.

00:29:21.616 --> 00:29:24.995
Especially in the morning,
it's not harsh on the skin.

00:29:27.747 --> 00:29:30.542
Turns out not all light is harmful.

00:29:31.793 --> 00:29:33.253
I get that now.

00:29:34.337 --> 00:29:37.757
I just need a little
light to do what I want.

00:29:39.134 --> 00:29:40.677
To write a song.

00:29:42.345 --> 00:29:49.811
I want to write songs for myself,
not for anyone else.

00:30:03.366 --> 00:30:05.285
I don't want the songs
I wrote before anymore.

00:30:06.036 --> 00:30:10.040
I want, that when people
hear the song I wrote,

00:30:11.041 --> 00:30:15.587
they’ll feel how light my
heart was while writing it.

00:30:16.171 --> 00:30:17.464
The real kind of relief.

00:30:19.007 --> 00:30:21.051
No freshly healed wounds.

00:30:23.928 --> 00:30:26.264
I want my wounds
to be completely healed

00:30:26.639 --> 00:30:28.516
before I take a new path in life.

00:30:29.434 --> 00:30:31.686
And the first step to that is...

00:30:34.314 --> 00:30:35.315
forgiving you.

00:30:41.863 --> 00:30:43.385
Ma, I forgive you.

00:30:51.706 --> 00:30:55.346
For all the hardships you caused us.

00:30:59.756 --> 00:31:01.883
For my siblings, for Papa.

00:31:09.641 --> 00:31:11.309
For leaving us behind.

00:31:19.567 --> 00:31:20.777
Don't worry,

00:31:21.820 --> 00:31:25.073
I'll do everything so what happened
to you won't happen again.

00:31:26.324 --> 00:31:31.538
I'll heal the wounds
of my siblings and Papa.

00:31:36.918 --> 00:31:39.421
But, I'll try to heal myself first.

00:31:46.177 --> 00:31:47.900
Thank you so much, Ma.

00:31:50.098 --> 00:31:51.266
Goodbye.

00:32:24.597 --> 00:32:29.185
When are you free? Can we
talk for a bit? I'll come see you.

00:32:43.151 --> 00:32:46.070
So here, you need to really
feel your rage in this scene.

00:32:46.070 --> 00:32:48.031
You have to be truly angry at him.

00:32:48.031 --> 00:32:49.657
Pour out all your emotions, okay?

00:32:49.991 --> 00:32:52.702
And for you, just keep defending,
ride along with her emotions.

00:32:52.952 --> 00:32:55.622
This scene has to be felt, it's the
most emotional part, it really is

00:32:55.622 --> 00:32:56.581
- the climax of our project.
- Okay.

00:32:56.581 --> 00:32:57.499
- Got it, director.
- Okay?

00:32:57.499 --> 00:32:58.641
Yes, Director.

00:32:58.666 --> 00:32:59.876
All right. Are you ready there?

00:33:02.253 --> 00:33:03.087
Sound?

00:33:03.375 --> 00:33:05.336
This is your dream.

00:33:05.381 --> 00:33:06.716
- To be a director.
- Camera?

00:33:07.701 --> 00:33:09.495
Three, two, one, action!

00:33:09.661 --> 00:33:10.904
Gina, what are you doing?

00:33:10.929 --> 00:33:13.264
Didn't I tell you? I'm only
bringing him in for work.

00:33:13.264 --> 00:33:14.390
She's just a friend.

00:33:14.474 --> 00:33:15.517
Why are you always with her?

00:33:15.517 --> 00:33:16.267
Do we always have to be like this?

00:33:16.267 --> 00:33:19.729
Just work? You’re always together.

00:33:30.281 --> 00:33:34.041
It's nice seeing you take
your film classes seriously.

00:33:36.246 --> 00:33:37.580
I'm enjoying it.

00:33:38.831 --> 00:33:42.502
Honestly, the joy and fulfillment
I feel now are different.

00:33:46.548 --> 00:33:48.007
Why did you decide to drop by here?

00:33:54.847 --> 00:33:56.099
I'm...

00:33:56.917 --> 00:33:59.294
I'm flying back to Spain next week.

00:34:06.651 --> 00:34:08.152
You're not mad, are you?

00:34:10.905 --> 00:34:12.365
Are you coming back?

00:34:15.410 --> 00:34:16.479
No.

00:34:19.080 --> 00:34:20.832
I'm not coming back.

00:34:24.168 --> 00:34:25.211
Why?

00:34:26.671 --> 00:34:28.381
Did you watch the interview?

00:34:28.798 --> 00:34:30.550
Yes, I did.

00:34:31.926 --> 00:34:33.678
You did a great job.

00:34:34.804 --> 00:34:37.056
There were a lot of positive reactions.

00:34:39.434 --> 00:34:42.145
Thank you for clearing my name, too.

00:34:45.273 --> 00:34:46.399
And how are you now?

00:34:47.650 --> 00:34:49.110
How are you feeling?

00:34:54.574 --> 00:34:58.911
If I said I'm okay, I would be lying.

00:35:02.373 --> 00:35:05.793
I'm not ready to be
part of your world yet, Arkin.

00:35:09.589 --> 00:35:11.341
Will you ever be ready?

00:35:16.262 --> 00:35:18.848
I can't put a deadline
on my healing process.

00:35:23.353 --> 00:35:26.022
Right now, I'm just focusing on myself.

00:35:27.231 --> 00:35:30.318
You know, I feel okay,

00:35:32.236 --> 00:35:34.405
and then all of a sudden, I don't.

00:35:36.974 --> 00:35:38.559
- I'm sorry, Via.
- No.

00:35:39.410 --> 00:35:41.204
You don't have to say sorry.

00:35:42.288 --> 00:35:45.750
Don't say sorry, because you did
a great job protecting me this time.

00:35:48.127 --> 00:35:49.545
I chose all of this.

00:35:50.755 --> 00:35:52.465
I chose to love you.

00:35:54.467 --> 00:35:55.968
And there's nothing wrong with that.

00:35:59.430 --> 00:36:03.184
But I don't want to pass all my
wounds and fears onto you, Kino.

00:36:05.853 --> 00:36:07.855
This is my battle to face.

00:36:09.315 --> 00:36:11.567
You don't need to get hurt for me.

00:36:13.111 --> 00:36:14.737
I'm just not ready yet.

00:36:15.988 --> 00:36:17.532
And you know that.

00:36:20.952 --> 00:36:23.454
I guess I pushed you way too hard.

00:36:25.206 --> 00:36:26.249
No.

00:36:26.958 --> 00:36:30.503
You just pushed me enough
to realize what I needed to do.

00:36:32.338 --> 00:36:35.675
I didn't expect you to face
so many people all at once.

00:36:37.301 --> 00:36:39.053
Sorry, I wasn't fast enough.

00:36:40.138 --> 00:36:41.681
But I hope you understood,

00:36:42.640 --> 00:36:44.892
that I couldn't speak impulsively.

00:36:45.518 --> 00:36:47.520
It could have just added fuel to the fire.

00:36:49.689 --> 00:36:51.357
You made the right choice.

00:36:54.026 --> 00:36:55.570
I understand.

00:36:56.674 --> 00:37:01.637
In everything you do, every decision
you make, you always think of me.

00:37:05.246 --> 00:37:08.249
I'm not here talking to you
because I needed time for myself.

00:37:09.667 --> 00:37:12.170
I needed time to make a decision.

00:37:16.549 --> 00:37:22.805
So you decided to leave?
To go back to Spain?

00:37:31.189 --> 00:37:34.192
Did it feel right, when
you made that decision?

00:37:48.664 --> 00:37:49.874
Yes.

00:37:55.296 --> 00:37:56.547
Okay then.

00:37:59.592 --> 00:38:01.052
Come on.

00:38:17.401 --> 00:38:18.778
Take care over there.

00:38:24.450 --> 00:38:29.080
And I hope your heart
finally finds its proper place.

00:38:40.508 --> 00:38:42.468
Kino, remember,

00:38:46.889 --> 00:38:50.810
you're the music I want
everyone to hear.

00:39:41.027 --> 00:39:42.028
Sweetheart...

00:39:42.121 --> 00:39:44.623
Here are the rest of your clothes,
I washed them last night.

00:39:45.656 --> 00:39:46.782
Thanks, Pa.

00:39:55.541 --> 00:39:58.044
Pa, don't be too sad, okay?

00:39:58.252 --> 00:40:00.296
Mira, Ysha, and Aidan are all here.

00:40:00.963 --> 00:40:02.506
They'll take care of you.

00:40:04.508 --> 00:40:08.930
You know, I'm not
really worried about that.

00:40:09.597 --> 00:40:15.895
I just want you to be here
so I know that you've eaten.

00:40:16.285 --> 00:40:19.372
So I know how you're feeling.

00:40:20.650 --> 00:40:23.486
Pa, don't worry about me. I'm fine.

00:40:24.987 --> 00:40:28.532
You just need to look after yourself.

00:40:28.532 --> 00:40:30.868
Always take your medicines, okay?

00:40:30.993 --> 00:40:33.454
Don't eat anything
you're not supposed to.

00:40:38.042 --> 00:40:39.168
Via...

00:40:40.836 --> 00:40:43.005
Papa's worried because-

00:40:44.340 --> 00:40:46.634
you don't really say anything

00:40:48.052 --> 00:40:49.845
when you're not okay.

00:40:51.722 --> 00:40:54.392
Just like what happened recently.

00:40:54.892 --> 00:40:58.396
Back then, we couldn’t
really say anything to you.

00:40:58.562 --> 00:41:04.276
Because you never
talk about how you feel.

00:41:07.780 --> 00:41:10.825
We know you're strong and that
you can handle things on your own.

00:41:11.117 --> 00:41:15.287
But you don't have to face it alone.

00:41:16.914 --> 00:41:24.255
We've seen and experienced how you broke
down, healed, and then got hurt again.

00:41:25.111 --> 00:41:30.116
But we're happy because it seems
like you're not giving up on healing again.

00:41:34.640 --> 00:41:36.517
You're really strong, Via.

00:41:39.270 --> 00:41:41.772
I'm strong because of all of you.

00:41:43.315 --> 00:41:46.444
And I keep getting stronger
because of your love.

00:41:58.831 --> 00:42:01.876
All right, I'll go grab
the rest of your clothes.

00:42:08.315 --> 00:42:09.233
Thanks.

00:42:09.258 --> 00:42:10.509
- Via.
- Yes?

00:42:10.509 --> 00:42:14.346
Luna stopped by this morning,
but you were still asleep.

00:42:14.346 --> 00:42:16.849
She said this is what you should
wear later when you go out.

00:42:17.266 --> 00:42:17.908
Huh?

00:42:17.933 --> 00:42:19.393
She's going to pick you up.

00:42:24.730 --> 00:42:25.524
What's taking so long?

00:42:25.524 --> 00:42:26.275
Okay, just keep your eyes closed.

00:42:26.275 --> 00:42:27.276
Where are we?

00:42:27.276 --> 00:42:28.527
- Just keep them closed, okay?
- You guys are taking forever.

00:42:28.527 --> 00:42:30.696
My hair's gonna turn gray from waiting.

00:42:31.155 --> 00:42:32.281
Looks pretty dark to me, bro.

00:42:32.281 --> 00:42:33.824
- Can't you see it? Right here.
- Wait a minute!

00:42:33.824 --> 00:42:34.992
- Here it is.
- Okay. This is it.

00:42:34.992 --> 00:42:36.368
We're here!

00:42:40.389 --> 00:42:41.849
Welcome home.

00:42:41.874 --> 00:42:43.334
Why did we come here?

00:42:43.334 --> 00:42:44.835
Why did you bring me here?

00:42:44.835 --> 00:42:48.255
Well, this is where everything
started, especially our friendship.

00:42:49.882 --> 00:42:52.718
Perfect timing, too, it's
the weekend. No classes.

00:42:54.178 --> 00:42:56.680
We can get dramatic later. Let's go?

00:42:57.865 --> 00:43:00.534
How about Luna? Is she coming?
There's no need to invite her.

00:43:00.559 --> 00:43:02.645
She's just taking care
of something. She'll follow later.

00:43:03.813 --> 00:43:05.689
Hey, do you remember that area?

00:43:05.981 --> 00:43:07.316
You remember? Look at it.

00:43:07.316 --> 00:43:08.734
Wow, it's still here?

00:43:09.193 --> 00:43:11.445
You're right. That thing's tough, bro.

00:43:12.113 --> 00:43:14.615
Just like our friendship.

00:43:15.407 --> 00:43:16.242
As if!

00:43:16.242 --> 00:43:17.868
Hey, that hurts.

00:43:17.868 --> 00:43:18.494
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:43:18.494 --> 00:43:22.498
You know, so many storms
have passed, but it's still there.

00:43:22.498 --> 00:43:23.874
Still standing.

00:43:24.542 --> 00:43:26.836
It didn't let itself get
completely destroyed.

00:43:27.169 --> 00:43:27.962
How about this-

00:43:27.962 --> 00:43:30.339
You remember when you two kissed?

00:43:30.714 --> 00:43:32.011
Do you guys remember that?

00:43:35.344 --> 00:43:36.220
Oh my-

00:43:36.220 --> 00:43:37.263
- Jerk!
- Fucker!

00:43:37.596 --> 00:43:39.056
You bastard! That was my first kiss!

00:43:39.056 --> 00:43:40.474
What? That was my first kiss too!

00:43:41.142 --> 00:43:42.601
- Ke's being such a jerk.
- You idiot.

00:43:42.601 --> 00:43:43.894
Such a jerk.

00:43:43.894 --> 00:43:44.870
I'd never with his ladle-face.

00:43:44.894 --> 00:43:46.397
That was crazy, you
two were like magnets.

00:43:46.438 --> 00:43:48.065
- I don't remember anything.
- Gross.

00:43:48.107 --> 00:43:49.859
Seriously, you guys.

00:43:49.859 --> 00:43:51.277
Let's just go!

00:43:55.656 --> 00:43:57.158
You might start kissing again.

00:43:57.575 --> 00:43:58.503
Hey!

00:45:00.137 --> 00:45:01.347
Stop pushing me.

00:45:01.680 --> 00:45:02.861
You're the one pushing,
my side is cramped.

00:45:02.885 --> 00:45:03.641
Your side is spacious.

00:45:03.641 --> 00:45:06.143
- You're so dramatic.
- We don't wanna get separated, huh?

00:45:06.936 --> 00:45:08.938
Hey, it's the music room. Via.

00:45:09.647 --> 00:45:11.690
- Oh, wow.
- We'll go this way.

00:45:11.690 --> 00:45:12.687
Hey.

00:45:13.734 --> 00:45:15.319
I thought there were no classes today?

00:45:15.653 --> 00:45:16.779
So much has changed.

00:45:16.779 --> 00:45:18.447
Miss, don't tell anyone, okay?

00:45:19.198 --> 00:45:23.535
The window here is gone now,
and they’ve got a drum set, a bass.

00:45:24.411 --> 00:45:26.163
They definitely have the budget now.

00:45:39.677 --> 00:45:40.970
Why are you laughing?

00:45:40.970 --> 00:45:41.971
Huh?

00:45:42.012 --> 00:45:43.514
Nothing, I just remembered something.

00:45:45.432 --> 00:45:46.350
I remembered Naya.

00:45:46.350 --> 00:45:47.367
What about her?

00:45:47.851 --> 00:45:49.728
You know, I was kinda jealous of her.

00:45:50.980 --> 00:45:52.106
What?

00:45:54.692 --> 00:45:57.152
No, not the serious kind of jealousy.

00:45:57.152 --> 00:45:59.015
You know that feeling...

00:45:59.822 --> 00:46:05.119
I just felt like giving you up, like you
preferred being with her than with me.

00:46:06.078 --> 00:46:08.789
So basically, you wanted to
keep me all to yourself, is that it?

00:46:08.789 --> 00:46:09.873
Am I right?

00:46:12.167 --> 00:46:13.711
It was just petty.

00:46:14.628 --> 00:46:16.588
It's just funny to think about.

00:46:17.256 --> 00:46:20.926
You might be forgetting you were
the one who pushed me toward Naya.

00:46:21.302 --> 00:46:23.012
I didn't even like her.

00:46:23.429 --> 00:46:27.266
I wanted to go to prom with you,
but you kept pushing me toward her.

00:46:27.474 --> 00:46:29.143
I didn't even get to ask you out.

00:46:30.394 --> 00:46:33.939
You have a way to hold grudges, Kino.

00:46:35.316 --> 00:46:37.526
Of course. I really do.

00:46:38.433 --> 00:46:39.851
- I think you're also forgetting-
- Right!

00:46:39.876 --> 00:46:41.044
- Let's just forget it. Come on.
- Huh?

00:46:41.069 --> 00:46:43.780
- You turned me down and then you rejected-
- Come on. Come on now.

00:46:47.119 --> 00:46:49.038
Your uniform feels kind of incomplete.

00:46:49.038 --> 00:46:50.873
You're missing your colorful hair clips.

00:46:50.873 --> 00:46:52.958
Yeah, the colored ones.

00:46:53.459 --> 00:46:55.669
Hey, but be careful there, okay?

00:46:58.047 --> 00:46:59.506
You too.

00:47:00.174 --> 00:47:04.219
No matter what happens, just remember
I'm always here for you, okay?

00:47:05.262 --> 00:47:09.350
Just call me anytime. As long as
you need me, I'll answer.

00:47:14.938 --> 00:47:16.648
I'm going to miss you.

00:47:16.982 --> 00:47:17.691
What-

00:47:17.691 --> 00:47:18.859
It's Sam, Sam answered!

00:47:18.859 --> 00:47:19.985
- Guys, Sam answered!
- Not the one-

00:47:19.985 --> 00:47:20.861
- Sam!
- It's Sam. Let's go.

00:47:20.861 --> 00:47:21.904
Is she there already?

00:47:22.071 --> 00:47:23.238
Good thing she answered.

00:47:26.241 --> 00:47:27.242
Hi, guys.

00:47:27.242 --> 00:47:28.577
- Hi, Sam!
- Hi!

00:47:28.577 --> 00:47:30.454
- Hi, Sam!
- You thought I was gonna miss this?

00:47:32.373 --> 00:47:34.833
See? I miss you guys.

00:47:35.042 --> 00:47:37.544
And I miss that place, too.

00:47:37.544 --> 00:47:40.923
Where I'd always find
my girl crying in the library.

00:47:41.465 --> 00:47:43.675
Time really flies, doesn't it?

00:47:43.884 --> 00:47:46.220
Wow, that sounded like it
came from some old person.

00:47:46.637 --> 00:47:49.973
And you'll be a single
old person forever.

00:47:50.432 --> 00:47:54.436
Okay? Who hasn't dated a
single person after their breakup?

00:47:55.437 --> 00:47:56.480
Who could that be?

00:47:56.480 --> 00:47:59.983
Well, it's my choice.
I'll be single forever.

00:48:00.275 --> 00:48:02.653
But if she comes back, I’m sure…

00:48:03.362 --> 00:48:05.614
If she comes back?
Then welcome to my life.

00:48:06.615 --> 00:48:08.200
Must be nice when they come back.

00:48:09.785 --> 00:48:11.537
She'll come back.

00:48:11.537 --> 00:48:14.752
If someone else from our group gets
married, you're coming back, okay, Via?

00:48:15.791 --> 00:48:17.835
So who's getting married next?

00:48:19.420 --> 00:48:21.797
Definitely not me, I don't
even have a boyfriend.

00:48:22.256 --> 00:48:24.133
How I wish I could be next.

00:48:24.967 --> 00:48:28.262
Hey, I still have some lingering
grudge about your ex, Sam.

00:48:29.263 --> 00:48:31.640
I miss you guys so much.

00:48:31.665 --> 00:48:33.667
I wanna be there, too.

00:48:34.583 --> 00:48:38.879
Anyway, Via, just always remember
that you may often be misunderstood.

00:48:39.189 --> 00:48:43.068
But what matters most is how
the people who truly know you see you.

00:48:43.777 --> 00:48:45.320
Thanks, Sam.

00:48:47.030 --> 00:48:48.532
We miss you here.

00:48:50.909 --> 00:48:52.119
What else can we do?

00:48:52.119 --> 00:48:55.080
You and Sam are both
far away from us now.

00:48:55.706 --> 00:48:57.833
Yeah, write to us, okay?

00:48:59.251 --> 00:49:01.753
Call as soon as you get there.

00:49:02.296 --> 00:49:04.173
I'll miss you, too.

00:49:05.966 --> 00:49:07.509
But I'm just leaving, right?

00:49:07.509 --> 00:49:10.345
That doesn't mean it's
the end of our friendship.

00:49:10.929 --> 00:49:15.559
And our friendship is one of the
greatest treasures I'll ever have.

00:49:17.186 --> 00:49:18.395
Thank you.

00:49:19.480 --> 00:49:23.692
Thank you for choosing me to be
your friend back in high school.

00:49:24.276 --> 00:49:28.155
I'll carry all those happy memories
with me for the rest of my life.

00:49:28.739 --> 00:49:30.852
And if one morning I wake
up and find myself back

00:49:30.877 --> 00:49:33.953
in high school, without a
doubt, without hesitation,

00:49:35.120 --> 00:49:37.641
I would still choose this
friendship all over again.

00:49:41.418 --> 00:49:42.669
Group hug!

00:49:42.669 --> 00:49:45.355
Join in, Sam!

00:49:45.380 --> 00:49:47.007
Virtual hug.

00:49:49.885 --> 00:49:51.477
Hey, hey! Wait, wait a minute.

00:49:51.502 --> 00:49:52.836
I've got some pens here.

00:49:52.868 --> 00:49:53.744
Let's write on each other's shirts, hurry.

00:49:53.769 --> 00:49:55.354
Give it to me. Me first.

00:49:56.058 --> 00:49:56.975
Wait, hold on.

00:49:56.975 --> 00:49:58.785
Don't write anything silly, okay?

00:49:58.810 --> 00:49:59.520
- There's nothing you can do.
- Via's uniform first.

00:49:59.520 --> 00:50:00.604
Make sure it's good.

00:50:00.604 --> 00:50:01.813
- Here.
- Nothing silly.

00:50:01.813 --> 00:50:02.856
Right here.

00:50:03.039 --> 00:50:04.651
Where are you ticklish?
Write where she's ticklish.

00:50:04.675 --> 00:50:05.836
No. No one's drawing...

00:50:06.109 --> 00:50:07.778
No one's drawing-

00:50:10.948 --> 00:50:13.909
Hey, you haven't written
on my blouse yet.

00:50:14.952 --> 00:50:17.996
Yeah. I can't think of anything to write.

00:50:30.842 --> 00:50:32.302
Are you happy, Via?

00:50:35.389 --> 00:50:36.473
Of course. I'm happy.

00:50:37.558 --> 00:50:38.684
I'm happy.

00:50:40.936 --> 00:50:42.729
How about you, Kino?
How are you?

00:50:43.355 --> 00:50:45.941
Has anyone asked
you that this past week?

00:50:45.941 --> 00:50:47.568
These past few days?

00:50:50.028 --> 00:50:51.154
Of course.

00:50:51.989 --> 00:50:53.365
Don't worry about me.

00:50:54.116 --> 00:50:56.368
Sevi even asked before you did.

00:50:58.662 --> 00:51:00.706
He will take care of you while I'm away.

00:51:01.373 --> 00:51:02.624
That's good.

00:51:03.000 --> 00:51:04.376
At least I know...

00:51:04.751 --> 00:51:08.714
there's someone who won't leave you
while I'm gone, no matter what happens.

00:51:13.176 --> 00:51:14.761
That was supposed to be you, though.

00:51:17.431 --> 00:51:18.932
But it's okay.

00:51:19.850 --> 00:51:22.352
I'll still love you no
matter how far you are.

00:51:36.158 --> 00:51:38.035
You'll still love me?

00:51:42.789 --> 00:51:45.167
When have I ever not loved you, Via?

00:51:53.592 --> 00:51:56.261
By the way, I already
thought of something to write.

00:52:03.518 --> 00:52:04.519
Turn around.

00:52:19.576 --> 00:52:21.286
There. All done.

00:52:35.852 --> 00:52:37.437
I'll see you tomorrow?

00:52:39.312 --> 00:52:40.382
Yes.

00:52:42.545 --> 00:52:44.282
Finally, I can send you off at the airport.

00:52:50.883 --> 00:52:53.135
Until our music fades again, Via.

00:52:56.113 --> 00:52:57.531
Goodbye, Via.

00:52:58.281 --> 00:52:59.574
I love you.

00:53:01.910 --> 00:53:03.537
Thank you, Kino.

00:53:06.623 --> 00:53:10.544
Always remember,
no matter what happens...

00:53:12.254 --> 00:53:14.965
I will always be your number one fan.

00:53:29.210 --> 00:53:32.380
You loved me the way I wanted to be loved.

00:53:32.482 --> 00:53:38.947
You made me feel every kind of love,
and that's why it's so hard to leave you.

00:53:39.089 --> 00:53:44.261
Your love was the greatest of all.
Your love was unconditional.

00:53:44.286 --> 00:53:47.539
You loved me even after I rejected you.

00:53:47.539 --> 00:53:51.626
You still loved me even when you knew
I couldn't return that love.

00:53:52.102 --> 00:53:55.272
You never once stopped loving me.

00:53:55.297 --> 00:53:58.258
It makes me sad that I
have to leave you again.

00:53:58.258 --> 00:54:04.055
But thank you, because even
if it hurts you, you're still happy for me.

00:54:04.055 --> 00:54:05.098
Let's go?

00:54:06.683 --> 00:54:07.686
All right, let's go.

00:54:07.934 --> 00:54:09.029
Let's go.

00:55:37.482 --> 00:55:40.026
You're my music.

00:56:35.957 --> 00:56:38.043
I promise, I won’t let you go.

00:56:38.043 --> 00:56:42.547
More handsome than the
most handsome guy! You wish, Sevi!

00:56:42.547 --> 00:56:43.840
City Council of Barcelona

00:56:56.061 --> 00:56:57.270
It’s so nice here, Via.

00:56:58.480 --> 00:57:00.148
I don’t have to hide my face.

00:57:02.692 --> 00:57:04.402
I have a concert in
Manila next month.

00:57:06.780 --> 00:57:09.824
It’s going to be my last one,
so I was hoping you could come.

00:57:10.825 --> 00:57:12.035
Your last concert?

00:57:12.911 --> 00:57:14.371
Let me tell you now.

00:57:14.621 --> 00:57:16.373
You won’t be able to convince me
to go back to the Philippines.

00:57:16.373 --> 00:57:18.166
I’m afraid of people.

00:57:20.168 --> 00:57:21.419
Of crowds.

00:57:23.755 --> 00:57:25.006
Please welcome—

00:57:25.674 --> 00:57:27.842
Larkin Sanchez!